<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Ademola Lookman is joining Fulham on a season-long loan from Red Bull Leipzig for a £1.8million fee. </p>

<p>The 22-year-old left Everton for Red Bull Leipzig last year in a £16.5m deal but made just 13 appearances last season.</p>

<p>The Bundesliga club are keen for the former England Under-21 winger to go out on loan and build up his confidence with more regular football.</p>

<p>Fulham are closing in on a deal to bring Ademola Lookman back to the Premier League</p>

<p>RB Leipzig sporting director Markus Krosche had earlier confirmed that Lookman could go out on loan.</p>

<p>He told German newspaper Bild: 'We are dealing with this matter, and it's possible that something will happen.</p>

<p>'Ademola hasn't played much, and you need playing time as a young player.'</p>

<p>Bild also claim the Londoner is keen on the switch</p>

